  ---
  How it works

  Authentication — Uses MSAL device-code flow on first run: it prints a
  URL and a short code; you open the URL in any browser and enter the
  code. The token is cached in .token_cache.bin so subsequent runs are
  silent.

  Rename — hello.txt → hello_2026-04-02T221530.txt (ISO timestamp,
  colon-free for filesystem safety).

  Upload — Via SharePoint REST API (Office365-REST-Python-Client),
  uploaded to the target_folder path in the site.

  Archive — Renamed file is moved to done/ on success; original name is
  restored if upload fails.

  ---
  Setup

  1. Fill in config.json with your real SharePoint URL, tenant ID, and app
   client ID.
    - The app registration needs AllSites.Write delegated permission (or
  Sites.ReadWrite.All).
  2. Install dependencies:
  pip3 install -r requirements.txt
  3. Run unit tests (no network needed):
  pytest test_upload.py -v -m unit
  4. Run the integration test (triggers device-code auth on first run):
  pytest test_upload.py -v -m integration
  5. Or run directly:
  python3 upload_to_sharepoint.py --filename hello.txt